HEADWORD: anaplerosis
<hw>an`a*ple*ro"sis</hw>
<pr>(⟦acr⟧n`⟦adot⟧*pl⟦esl⟧*r⟦omac⟧"s⟦icr⟧s)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>
<sn>1.</sn> <fld>(Med.)</fld> <def>A filling up; restoring a defective
part; especially, promoting granulation of wounds or ulcers.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>AS</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Med)</fld> <def>The process of restoring the
depleted cellular metabolic intermediate pools; most commonly used to
refer to the restoration of the citric acid cycle intermediates
pool.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>AS</source>]</p>

<p><ent>anaplerotic</ent>⟦br⟧
